SARASIN & PARTNERS LLP Revenue and Financial Data

   Sarasin & Partners manages investments for private clients, charities, family groups, and insurance companies and other institutional investors. Utilizing asset allocation strategies focused on recurring income and long-term investments, the company has more than £11 billion ($17 billion) of assets under management. Products and services include individual savings accounts (ISAs), personal equity plans (PEPs), pensions, and specialized investment programs focused on global equities, bonds, real estate, and balanced strategies. A subsidiary of Switzerland-based Bank Sarasin, it operates offices in London and Dublin. The Netherlands-based Rabobank Group sold its stake in Bank Sarasin to Safra Group in 2012.
  







