Home/ Team
















Meet the team




Jamie Black
Partner, Head of Private Clients - Sarasin & Partners LLP, CEO - Sarasin Asset Management Ltd
Jamie is Head of our Private Client team with responsibility for client relationship management, new business development and products. Prior to joining Sarasin & Partners, Jamie was at NCL Investments Ltd having joined the City days before the 1987 stock market crash.
Jamie has a MA Hons in Modern Languages from Cambridge University and holds the Private Client Investment Advice and Management Certificate (PCIAM), the Investment Management Certificate (IMC), and is a Stock Exchange Registered Representative.





Ben Human
Quant Analyst
Ben focuses on research of quant strategies and supports day-to-day management of systematic products. He holds a Mechanical Engineering degree from the University of Durham.
Fluid dynamics is one of Ben's research interests and the area he  concentrated on during his engineering programme. He is highly proficient in several programming languages including Matlab, C#, and C++. Prior to Sarasin, Ben worked for the investment team at Prospect Wealth Management, a part of Raymond James.





Alex Jevons
Associate Partner – Sarasin & Partners LLP, Investment Director - Sarasin Asset Management Ltd
Alex works with the Partners on domestic and international portfolios. Alex is also a member of the Private Client Thematic Equity Committee. Prior to joining Sarasin & Partners, Alex worked at Dexion Capital, Financial Risk Management (FRM), Hedge, and Katten Muchin Rosenman Cornish LLP. 
Alex is a graduate of the University of Edinburgh. 





Sophie Jewson
Business Development, Private Clients
Sophie’s primary responsibility is to manage and develop relationships with potential clients, as well as a range of intermediaries who represent private individuals and families, to enable a steady flow of new business opportunities.
She joined the Private Client team at Sarasin & Partners in January 2012. Prior to this, Sophie spent 4 years with a Corporate Finance boutique in Mayfair. The first couple of years of her career were spent as a chef, followed by a short time as a recruitment consultant.
Sophie holds the Investment Management Certificate (IMC).





Andrea Nardon
Partner, Fund Manager, Head of Quant
Andrea is the fund manager of Sarasin & Partners' systematic franchise, and currently manages $1 billion in quant strategies. 
He joined Sarasin & Partners in 2006 from Deka Investment (Frankfurt, Germany) where he worked for four years managing hedge fund and long-only strategies. Prior to that, he worked at Commerzbank Asset Management for three years as Quant Strategist in the equity team.
Andrea graduated in Economics from the University of Venice (Italy), and spent a year in the Department of Mathematics focusing on neural networks and artifical intelligence.





Iuliia Shpak
Systematic Strategies Specialist
Iuliia joined Sarasin & Partners in February 2016 to support the development of the systematic business. She is also currently pursuing a PhD in Finance, focusing on asset pricing; namely, speculative bubbles and momentum anomalies in commodity and equity markets.
Before joining Sarasin & Partners, Iuliia worked for eight years in the business intelligence industry in the Middle East and Europe. She holds an MSc in Operational Research from the London School of Economics.





John Soler
Senior Associate Partner  - Sarasin & Partners LLP, Investment Manager - Sarasin Asset Management Ltd
John is responsible for the management of UK and international, including US, private client portfolios. Prior to joining Sarasin & Partners, John was with Merrill Lynch Portfolio Managers for 15 years. 
John attended Tulane University, New Orleans and has a degree in Finance & Economics. 





Nick Wood
Senior Associate Partner - Sarasin & Partners LLP, Director - Sarasin Asset Management Ltd
Nick is responsible for the management of UK and international private client portfolios, on behalf of both Sarasin & Partners, as well as Sarasin Asset Management, a subsidiary of Sarasin & Partners, which solely manages portfolios for US investors. 
Nick has a BA Hons. degree in Languages for Business (German) from Oxford Brookes University.















